To investigate the influence of underdamped vibrational motion on the charge separation of strongly bound electron–hole pairs, we consider a one-dimensional chain consisting of N sites, composed of an electron donor in contact with a chain of (N−1) electron acceptors, as schematically shown in Fig. 1a. Two and three-dimensional donor–acceptor networks will be considered later. The electronic Hamiltonian is modeled by1He=∑k=0N−1Ωkkk+∑k=0N−2Jk,k+1(kk+1+h.c.),\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
